OL,3,COngoing cuts to domestic services a
OL,4,Cbigger concern than axing of Hardtalk
OL,6,FHardtalk is usually shown in the UK
OL,7,Fovernight or at the weekends.
OL,9,FIts principal slot is on BBC World.
OL,11,FJust how much of its budget came from
OL,12,Fthe licence fee and how much came from
OL,13,Fthe commercial budget of BBC World?
OL,15,FI say this not to defend the decision
OL,16,Fto axe Hardtalk but to try to ensure
OL,17,Fthe controversy it has generated in
OL,18,Fcertain quarters does not distract
OL,19,Ffrom the bigger question of BBC
OL,20,Ffunding and ensuring the corporation
OL,21,Fhas the resources it needs.
